son\n| writer3         =\n| extra3          = {{hlist|[[Chris Milk]]|West}}\n| length3         = 4:05\n\n| title4          = Two Words\n| note4           = featuring Mos Def, Freeway and The Harlem Boys Choir\n| writer4         = \n| extra4          = {{hlist|West|Coodie & Chike}}\n| length4         = 4:43\n\n| title5          = Jesus Walks\n| note5           = Church version\n| extra5          = [[Michael Haussman]]\n| length5         = 4:04\n\n| title6          = Jesus Walks\n| note6           = Chris Milk version\n| extra6          = Milk\n| length6         = 4:06\n\n| title7          = Jesus Walks\n| note7           = Street version\n| extra7          = {{hlist|West|Coodie & Chike}}\n| length7         = 4:18\n\n| title8          = Jesus Walks\n| note8           = Making of the video\n| extra8          = \n| length8         = 66:56\n\n| title9          = The New Workout Plan\n| note9           = Extended version featuring Fonzworth Bentley\n| extra9          = {{hlist|[[Director X|Little X]]|West}}\n| length9         = 8:06\n\n| total_length    = 104:46\n}}\n\n=== Sample credits ===\n* \"We Don't Care\" contains samples of \"I Just Wanna Stop\", written by Ross Vannelli and performed by The Jimmy Castor Bunch.\n* \"All Falls Down\" contains interpolations of \"Mystery of Iniquity\", written and performed by [[Lauryn Hill]].\n* \"Spaceship\" contains samples of \"[[Distant Lover]]\", written by [[Marvin Gaye]], [[Gwen Gordy Fuqua]] and Sandra Greene, and performed by Marvin Gaye.\n* \"Jesus Walks\" contains samples of \"Walk with Me\", performed by The ARC Choir and \"[[(Don't Worry) If There's a Hell Below, We're All Going to Go]]\", written and performed by [[Curtis Mayfield]].\n* \"Never Let Me Down\" contains samples of \"Maybe It's the Power of Love\", written by [[Michael Bolton]] and [[Bruce Kulick]], and performed by [[Blackjack (American band)|Blackjack]].\n* \"Slow Jamz\" contains samples of \"[[A House Is Not a Home (song)|A House Is Not a Home]]\", written by [[Burt Bacharach]] and [[Hal David]], and performed by [[Luther Vandross]].\n* \"School Spirit\" contains samples of \"[[Spirit in the Dark (song)|Spirit in the Dark]]\", written and performed by [[Aretha Franklin]].\n* \"Two Words\" contains samples of \"Peace & Love (Amani Na Mapenzi) \u2013 Movement IV (Encounter)\", written by Lou Wilson, Ric Wilson and Carlos Wilson, and performed by [[Mandrill (band)|Mandrill]].\n* \"Through the Wire\" contains samples of \"[[Through the Fire (song)|Through the Fire]]\", written by [[David Foster]], Tom Keane and [[Cynthia Weil]], and performed by [[Chaka Khan]].\n* \"Family Business\" contains samples of \"Fonky Thang\", written by [[Terry Callier]] and [[Charles Stepney]], and performed by [[The Dells]].\n* \"Last Call\" contains samples of \"Mr. Rockefeller\", written by Jerry Blatt and [[Bette Midler]], and performed by Bette Midler.\n\n== Personnel ==\nCredits adapted from liner notes.<ref name=linernotes>{{cite AV media notes|others=Kanye West |title=The College Dropout |year=2004 |publisher=Roc-A-Fella Records |id=}}</ref><ref name=\"credits\">{{cite journal|date=April 2, 2004|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/the-college-dropout-mw0000326741/credits|title=Credits: The College Dropout|publisher=AllMusic. All Media Guide|accessdate=July 11, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140307000051/http://www.allmusic.com/album/the-college-dropout-mw0000326741/credits|archivedate=March 7, 2014}}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Musicians===\n*[[John Legend]] \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 3)}}, additional vocals {{small|(tracks 2, 6, 7, 11, 21)}}, background vocals {{small|(track 8)}}, piano {{small|(track 3)}}\n*[[DeRay Davis|DeRay]] \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(tracks 1, 5, 14, 16, 17)}}\n*[[The World Famous Tony Williams|Tony Williams]] \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 5, 6, 15, 17, 21)}}\n*Sumeke Rainey \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(tracks 9, 11)}}\n*[[Tracie Spencer]] \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 12)}}, background vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n*Riccarda Watkins \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 2)}}\n*Candis Brown \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 10)}},\n*Brandi Kuykenvall \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 10)}}\n*Tiera Singleton \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 10)}}\n*[[Aisha Tyler]] \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 12)}}\n*Thomasina Atkins \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 20)}}\n*Linda Petty \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 20)}}\n*Beverly McCargo \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 20)}}\n*Lavel Mena \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 20)}}\n*Thai Jones \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 20)}}\n*Kevin Shannon \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 20)}}\n*Tarey Torae \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 20)}}\n*[[Rude Jude]] \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(track 22)}}\n*Terence Hardy \u2013 \"kids\" vocals {{small|(track 2)}}\n*Diamond Alabi-Isama \u2013 \"kids\" vocals {{small|(track 2)}}\n*James \"JT\" Knight \u2013 \"kids\" vocals {{small|(track 2)}}\n*[[Keyshia Cole]] \u2013 background vocals {{small|(track 2)}}\n*Ervin \"EP\" Pope \u2013 keyboards {{small|(tracks 8, 12)}}, piano {{small|(tracks 5, 11, 17, 21)}}\n*Glenn Jefferey \u2013 guitars {{small|(tracks 8, 12, 21)}}\n*Keenan \"Kee-note\" Holloway \u2013 bass {{small|(tracks 8, 12)}}, additional bass {{small|(track 21)}}\n*Frank Walker \u2013 percussion {{small|(tracks 3, 8, 12)}}\n*[[Ken Lewis (musician)|Ken Lewis]] \u2013 acoustic guitar {{small|(track 4)}}, sample recreation and performance {{small|(track 8)}}, additional instrumentation {{small|(track 20)}}, guitar, bass, keyboard, percussion, vocal {{small|(track 21)}}\n*Eric \"E-Bass\" Johnson \u2013 guitars {{small|(tracks 4, 11)}}\n*Bosko \u2013 talkbox {{small|(track 11)}}\n*Keith Slattery \u2013 keyboards {{small|(track 18)}}\n*Scott Ward \u2013 bass guitar {{small|(track 19)}}\n*Josh Zandman \u2013 piano {{small|(track 20)}}\n*[[Miri Be